<html>
	<head>
		<title>BCM_LOADFILE</title>
	</head>
	<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
		<p><font color="#000000" size="4"><strong>BCM_LOADFILE</strong></font></p>
		<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="3" width="100%">
			<tr>
				<td width="100%" bgcolor="#e6e6e6"><pre>BCM_LOADFILE
	wParam = ( WPARAM )( BOOL )bForce;
	lParam = ( LPARAM )( LPCTSTR )lpszFilename;</pre>
				</td>
			</tr>
		</table>
		<p>Loads the specified file into the control.</p>
		<UL>
			<LI>
				Can return any of the following return codes.</LI>
			<ul type="disc">
				<LI>
					BCMR_OK<BR>
					No problems.</LI>
				<LI>
					BCMR_ERROR
					<BR>
					An error occured during the file loading. Use GetLastError() to find out more 
					about the error.</LI>
				<LI>
					BCMR_SAVEFIRST<BR>
					The&nbsp;current control contents has been modified. The contents should be 
					saved first. If the <EM>bForce</EM> parameter has been set to a non-zero value 
					this return code will not be generated.</LI></ul>
		</UL>
		<dl>
			<dt><em>bForce</em>
				<dd>
					When this is non-zero the specified file is loaded into the control wether the 
					current contents is modified or not. When this is zero and the current control 
					contents is modified BCMR_SAVEFIRST is returned.</dd>
		</dl>
		<dl>
			<dt><em>lpszFilename</em>
				<dd>
					A pointer to a 0-terminated string which contains the fully qualified path of 
					the file to load. This parameter is required.</dd>
		</dl>
	</body>
</html>
